\"| [[Bernie Parrish]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Defensive Back|DB]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1959-1966\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 74\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Tony Adamle]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Linebacker|LB]]/[[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1947\u20131951, 1954\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=2| 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 40\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Erich Barnes]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Defensive Back|DB]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1965-71\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 51\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Eddie Johnson (linebacker)|Eddie Johnson]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Linebacker|LB]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1981-1990\n|}\n\n===Pro Bowlers===\n{{main|List of Cleveland Browns Pro Bowlers}}\n\n===Retired uniform numbers===\n{{Cleveland Browns retired numbers}}\n\n===Ring of Honor===\nBeginning in 2010, the Browns established a Ring of Honor, honoring the greats from the past by having their names displayed around the upper deck of FirstEnergy Stadium. The inaugural class in the Browns Ring of Honor was unveiled during the home opener on September 19, 2010, and featured the 16 Hall of Famers listed above who went into the Hall of Fame as Browns.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Davis|first1=Nate|title=Sixteen inaugural members of Cleveland Browns Ring of Honor unveiled|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/thehuddle/post/2010/08/sixteen-inaugural-members-of-cleveland-browns-ring-of-honor-unveiled/1|accessdate=May 5, 2017|work=USA Today|date=August 26, 2010}}</ref> In 2018, [[Joe Thomas (offensive tackle)|Joe Thomas]] was entered into the Ring of Honor with the number 10,363 - commemorating his NFL record of consecutive snaps played on offense.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaw|first=Courtney|title=Former Browns player Joe Thomas' snap streak added to Ring of Honor|url=http://www.news5cleveland.com/sports/browns/former-browns-player-joe-thomas-snap-streak-added-to-ring-of-honor|website=News5Cleveland.com|date=October 14, 2018|access-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref> In 2019, four-time Pro Bowl linebacker [[Clay Matthews Jr.|Clay Matthews]] was entered into the Ring of Honor.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gribble|first=Andrew|title=Browns to induct LB Clay Matthews into Ring of Honor|url=https://www.clevelandbrowns.com/news/browns-to-induct-lb-clay-matthews-into-ring-of-honor|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=ClevelandBrowns.com|date=July 31, 2019|access-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Williams|first=Charean|title=Browns to induct Clay Matthews into their Ring of Honor|url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2019/07/31/browns-to-induct-clay-matthews-into-their-ring-of-honor|website=NBCSports.com|date=July 31, 2019|access-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style= \"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}}\" | Cleveland Browns Ring of Honor\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Inducted\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | No.\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Name\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Position(s)\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Tenure\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=16| 2010\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 32\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Jim Brown]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Fullback (American football)|FB]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1957\u20131965\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Paul Brown]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Head coach]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1946\u20131962\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 64\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Joe DeLamielleure]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Offensive guard|OG]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1980\u20131984\n|-\n| style=\"t