 2018, [[Joe Thomas (offensive tackle)|Joe Thomas]] was entered into the Ring of Honor with the number 10,363 - commemorating his NFL record of consecutive snaps played on offense.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaw|first=Courtney|title=Former Browns player Joe Thomas' snap streak added to Ring of Honor|url=http://www.news5cleveland.com/sports/browns/former-browns-player-joe-thomas-snap-streak-added-to-ring-of-honor|website=News5Cleveland.com|date=October 14, 2018|access-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref> In 2019, four-time Pro Bowl linebacker [[Clay Matthews Jr.|Clay Matthews]] was entered into the Ring of Honor.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gribble|first=Andrew|title=Browns to induct LB Clay Matthews into Ring of Honor|url=https://www.clevelandbrowns.com/news/browns-to-induct-lb-clay-matthews-into-ring-of-honor|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=ClevelandBrowns.com|date=July 31, 2019|access-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Williams|first=Charean|title=Browns to induct Clay Matthews into their Ring of Honor|url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2019/07/31/browns-to-induct-clay-matthews-into-their-ring-of-honor|website=NBCSports.com|date=July 31, 2019|access-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style= \"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}}\" | Cleveland Browns Ring of Honor\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Inducted\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | No.\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Name\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Position(s)\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Cleveland Browns}};\" | Tenure\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=16| 2010\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 32\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Jim Brown]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Fullback (American football)|FB]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1957\u20131965\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"te