{"title_page": "University of Da Nang", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n| name = '''University of Da Nang'''\n| native_name = \u0110\u1ea1i h\u1ecdc \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng\n| image = Dai Hoc Da Nang Sign.JPG\n| image_upright = 1.15\n| image_alt = Blue sign with silver text\n| established = April 4, 1994\n| type = [[Public university|Public]]\n| president = Nguyen Ngoc Vu \n| vice-president = Ngo Van Duong<br/>Le Thanh Bac<br/>Le Quang Son\n| students = 50,000<ref name=\"acadaff\" />\n| academic_staff = 905<ref name=\"acadaff\">http://www.udn.vn/En/info.asp?Info=4</ref>\n| administrative_staff = 433<ref name=\"acadaff\" />\n| city = [[Da Nang]]\n| country = [[Vietnam]]\n| website = {{URL|http://www.udn.vn/english}}\n}}\n\nThe '''University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng''' ({{lang-vi|\u0110\u1ea1i h\u1ecdc \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng|links=no}}) is a regional multi-disciplinary [[university]] in [[Central Vietnam]].\n\n==Organizational structure==\nThe University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng was established on April 4, 1994, upon the rearrangement and reorganization of the former institutes:\n*Polytechnic University\n*\u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng Foreign Language Teachers Training College\n*Quang Nam Teachers Training College\n*Nguyen Van Troi Vocational School\n\nIn line with [[Hue University|Hu\u1ebf University]] and [[Thai Nguyen University]], the University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng is one of three regional universities in Vietnam which have a wide variety of training levels.\n\nAs of 2020, the University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng consisted of:\n* Eight members\n#[[Da Nang University of Technology|The University of Technology]] (CT)\n#The University of Technology and Education\n#[[Da Nang University of Economics|The University of Economics]] (CEs)\n#[[Da Nang University of Foreign LanguageStudies|The University of Foreign Language Studies]] (UFLS)\n#The University of Education (CE)\n#Vietnam-Korea University of Information and Communication Technology (VKU)\n#VNUK Institute of Research and Executive education (VNUK)\n#School of Medicine and Pharmacy\n* 17 centers for training and upgrading, scientific research promotion and technology transfer\n* Journal of Science and Technology\n\n==Development orientation==\nThe University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng will continue to consolidate the assets such as laboratories, workshops, libraries; expand the scope and training majors with focus on high technologies, renovating the training curricula, improving teaching methodologies, increasing the quality of training, applying scientific research results to practice to meet the renovation of national economy.\nThe Prime Minister has approved the master plan for the University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng, including an area of 300 hectares at Hoa Quy-Dien Ngoc, 15&nbsp;km from \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng City center to the south-east. The preparation work for the construction site and the infrastructure have begun.\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Empty section|date=July 2014}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.udn.vn/ The University of Da Nang]\n*[http://dut.udn.vn/ Danang University of Technology]\n*[http://www.due.udn.vn/ Danang University of Economics]\n*[http://www.ued.udn.vn/ Danang University of Education]\n*[http://ufl.udn.vn/eng/]\n*[http://www.dct.udn.vn/ Danang College of Technology]\n*[http://www.cit.udn.vn/ The Danang College of Information Technology]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140625175952/http://www.fmp.udn.vn/ The Danang Faculty of Medicine and phamarcy]\n*[http://www.kontum.udn.vn/ The Campus in Kontum]\n*[http://www.vnuk.edu.vn/ VNUK Institute of Research and Executive Education]\n\n{{coord|16.0709|N|108.2194|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Universities in Da Nang]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n| name = '''University of Da Nang'''\n| native_name = \u0110\u1ea1i h\u1ecdc \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng\n| image = Dai Hoc Da Nang Sign.JPG\n| image_upright = 1.15\n| image_alt = Blue sign with silver text\n| established = April 4, 1994\n| type = [[Public university|Public]]\n| president = Nguyen Ngoc Vu \n| vice-president = Ngo Van Duong<br/>Le Thanh Bac<br/>Le Quang Son\n| students = 50,000<ref name=\"acadaff\" />\n| academic_staff = 905<ref name=\"acadaff\">http://www.udn.vn/En/info.asp?Info=4</ref>\n| administrative_staff = 433<ref name=\"acadaff\" />\n| city = [[Da Nang]]\n| country = [[Vietnam]]\n| website = {{URL|http://www.udn.vn/english}}\n}}\n\nThe '''University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng''' ({{lang-vi|\u0110\u1ea1i h\u1ecdc \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng|links=no}}) is a regional multi-disciplinary [[university]] in [[Central Vietnam]].\n\n==Organizational structure==\nThe University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng was established on April 4, 1994, upon the rearrangement and reorganization of the former institutes:\n*Polytechnic University\n*\u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng Foreign Language Teachers Training College\n*Quang Nam Teachers Training College\n*Nguyen Van Troi Vocational School\n\nIn line with [[Hue University|Hu\u1ebf University]] and [[Thai Nguyen University]], the University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng is one of three regional universities in Vietnam which have a wide variety of training levels.\n\nAs of 2020, the University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng consisted of:\n* Eight members\n#[[Da Nang University of Technology|The University of Technology]] (CT)\n#The University of Technology and Education\n#[[Da Nang University of Economics|The University of Economics]] (CEs)\n#[[Da Nang University of Foreign LanguageStudies|The University of Foreign Language Studies]] (UFLS)\n#The University of Education (CE)\n#Vietnam-Korea University of Infomation and Communication Technology (VKU)\n#VNUK Institute of Research and Executive education (VNUK)\n#School of Medicine and Pharmacy\n* 17 centers for training and upgrading, scientific research promotion and technology transfer\n* Journal of Science and Technology\n\n\n==Development orientation==\nThe University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng will continue to consolidate the assets such as laboratories, workshops, libraries; expand the scope and training majors with focus on high technologies, renovating the training curricula, improving teaching methodologies, increasing the quality of training, applying scientific research results to practice to meet the renovation of national economy.\nThe Prime Minister has approved the master plan for the University of \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng, including an area of 300 hectares at Hoa Quy-Dien Ngoc, 15&nbsp;km from \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng City center to the south-east. The preparation work for the construction site and the infrastructure have begun.\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Empty section|date=July 2014}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.udn.vn/ The University of Da Nang]\n*[http://dut.udn.vn/ Danang University of Technology]\n*[http://www.due.udn.vn/ Danang University of Economics]\n*[http://www.ued.udn.vn/ Danang University of Education]\n*[http://ufl.udn.vn/eng/]\n*[http://www.dct.udn.vn/ Danang College of Technology]\n*[http://www.cit.udn.vn/ The Danang College of Information Technology]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140625175952/http://www.fmp.udn.vn/ The Danang Faculty of Medicine and phamarcy]\n*[http://www.kontum.udn.vn/ The Campus in Kontum]\n*[http://www.vnuk.edu.vn/ VNUK Institute of Research and Executive Education]\n\n{{coord|16.0709|N|108.2194|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Universities in Da Nang]]\n", "name_user": "Kaltenmeyer", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOrganizational structure:clean up, replaced: Infomation \u2192 Information", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Da_Nang"}
{"title_page": "All That's Left Is Love", "text_new": "{{Infobox song|name=All That's Left Is Love|cover=Angels & Airwaves - All That's Left Is Love.jpg|alt=|border=yes|type=single|artist=[[Angels & Airwaves]]|album=|released={{Start date|2020|04|16|mf=yes}}|format=* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]|recorded=|studio=|genre=<!-- Please source genres -->|length={{Duration|m=4|s=05}}|label=[[Rise Records]]|writer=* [[Tom DeLonge]]\n* [[Ilan Rubin]]\n* Aaron Rubin|producer=* Aaron Rubin\n* Angels & Airwaves|prev_title=[[Rebel Girl (Angels & Airwaves song)|Rebel Girl]]|prev_year=2019|next_title=|next_year=}}\"'''All That's Left Is Love'''\" is a song by the American rock band, [[Angels & Airwaves]]. The song was released on April 16, 2020 as the second single from the band's upcoming sixth album. The song was written by [[Tom DeLonge]], [[Ilan Rubin]], and Aaron Rubin.\n\n== Background ==\n\"All That's Left Is Love\" was written directly about the global impact of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]], and about being optimistic of the future during troubling times. In a public statement, DeLonge revealed the message of the song:<blockquote>\u201cFriends \u2014 as we are all stuck at home and watching these unfortunate world events unfold, we couldn\u2019t help but notice little glimmers of light showing across the globe \u2014 revealing the positive side of humanity that sometimes gets lost in our day-to-day lives. That, ultimately, is what this band has been about since day one \u2014 HOPE. With all of that in mind, we decided to channel our feelings into a song.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-the-uplifting-video-for-angels-and-airwaves-new-single-all-thats-left-is-love-2648257|title=Angels And Airwaves share uplifting new single 'All That\u2019s Left Is Love'|date=2020-04-16|website=NME Music News, Reviews, Videos, Galleries, Tickets and Blogs {{!}} NME.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n== Release and reception ==\nThe band began to tease the song on their social media platforms before officially announcing its release to be April 16, 2020. It was premiere on [[Apple Music]]'s [[Beats 1]] radio station before being released digitally. Alongside the release, it was revealed that all proceeds from the song would be donated to the nonprofit organization [[Feeding America]]'s COVID-19 relief fund. During an interview with Apple Music's Zane Lowe, DeLonge discussed the decision to donate all of the song's profits to the charity:<blockquote>\u201cI\u2019ve handed out food on holidays and for people in need. I\u2019ve gone to schools and handed out food to a lot of these kids only get their meals at school. And a lot of people think that the United States obviously is a more wealthy country than other, but there\u2019s still so much poverty here. As you know, you live in Los Angeles, and so you can see that there\u2019s a disparity between the classes. It was very simple for me to make one phone call and say, \u2018Why don\u2019t we do this? Because this is something that everybody needs right now. People can\u2019t take care of their families. Kids are not in schools where they\u2019re getting their only meal of the day.\u2019 It kind of worked out, and that\u2019s how you know it\u2019s meant to be. I\u2019m super proud to be with Feeding America on this.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/angels-and-airwaves-new-song-all-thats-left-is-love-985262/|title=Angels and Airwaves Unveil New Song 'All That's Left Is Love'|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|last2=Kreps|first2=Daniel|date=2020-04-16|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref></blockquote>The song was met with mostly positive feedback. [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s Gil Kaufman felt that the song's second verse \"pretty well sums up what a lot of us are feeling these days\" in reference to the social impact of the pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/9359780/angels-and-airwaves-all-thats-left-is-love|title=Angels & Airwaves&#39; &#39;All That&#39;s Left Is Love&#39; Single: Listen|date=2020-04-16|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Josiah Hughes of [[Exclaim!]] called the song \"another inspiring piece of uplifting alt pop. The song is four minutes long, but never overstays its welcome as it builds and expands.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/tom_delonges_angels_and_airwaves_return_with_hopeful_new_single_all_thats_left_is_love|title=Tom DeLonge's Angels & Airwaves Return with Hopeful New Single \"All That's Left Is Love\"|website=exclaim.ca|language=en-ca|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Emily Tan of [[Spin (magazine)|SPIN]] felt that the song \"starts off slow, but then grows into a pretty empowering anthem.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2020/04/angels-airwaves-make-epic-return-with-all-thats-left-is-love/|title=Angels & Airwaves Drop 'All That's Left Is Love'|date=2020-04-16|website=Spin|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n\n* '''Digital download'''<ref>{{Citation|title=All That's Left Is Love - Single by Angels & Airwaves|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/all-thats-left-is-love-single/1507962753|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n# \"All That's Left Is Love\" \u2013 4:05\n\n== Personnel ==\n'''Angels & Airwaves'''\n\n* [[Tom DeLonge]] \u2013 vocals, keyboards, synthesizers, [[songwriting]], [[Record producer|producer]]\n* [[Ilan Rubin]] \u2013 drums, backing vocals, guitars, bass guitar, keyboards, songwriting, producer\n* [[David Kennedy (musician)|David Kennedy]] \u2013 producer\n\n'''Production'''<ref>{{Citation|last=|first=|title=All That's Left Is Love|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nx7EP-Jbj9k|volume=|pages=|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n* Aaron Rubin \u2013 producer, songwriting, engineer\n* Ben Moore \u2013 engineer\n* [[Tony Hoffer]] \u2013 engineer\n* Tom Baker \u2013 engineer\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{MetroLyrics song|angels-and-airwaves|all-that's-left-is-love}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n{{Angels & Airwaves}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song|name=All That's Left Is Love|cover=Angels & Airwaves - All That's Left Is Love.jpg|alt=|border=yes|type=single|artist=[[Angels & Airwaves]]|album=|released={{Start date|2020|04|16|mf=yes}}|format=* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]|recorded=|studio=|genre=<!-- Please source genres -->|length={{Duration|m=4|s=05}}|label=[[Rise Records|Rise]]|writer=* [[Tom DeLonge]]\n* [[Ilan Rubin]]\n* Aaron Rubin|producer=* Aaron Rubin\n* Angels & Airwaves|prev_title=[[Rebel Girl (Angels & Airwaves song)|Rebel Girl]]|prev_year=2019|next_title=|next_year=}}\"'''All That's Left Is Love'''\" is a song by the American rock band, [[Angels & Airwaves]]. The song was released on April 16, 2020 as the second single from the band's upcoming sixth album. The song was written by [[Tom DeLonge]], [[Ilan Rubin]], and Aaron Rubin.\n\n== Background ==\n\"All That's Left Is Love\" was written directly about the global impact of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]], and about being optimistic of the future during troubling times. In a public statement, DeLonge revealed the message of the song:<blockquote>\u201cFriends \u2014 as we are all stuck at home and watching these unfortunate world events unfold, we couldn\u2019t help but notice little glimmers of light showing across the globe \u2014 revealing the positive side of humanity that sometimes gets lost in our day-to-day lives. That, ultimately, is what this band has been about since day one \u2014 HOPE. With all of that in mind, we decided to channel our feelings into a song.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-the-uplifting-video-for-angels-and-airwaves-new-single-all-thats-left-is-love-2648257|title=Angels And Airwaves share uplifting new single 'All That\u2019s Left Is Love'|date=2020-04-16|website=NME Music News, Reviews, Videos, Galleries, Tickets and Blogs {{!}} NME.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n== Release and reception ==\nThe band began to tease the song on their social media platforms before officially announcing its release to be April 16, 2020. It was premiere on [[Apple Music]]'s [[Beats 1]] radio station before being released digitally. Alongside the release, it was revealed that all proceeds from the song would be donated to the nonprofit organization [[Feeding America]]'s COVID-19 relief fund. During an interview with Apple Music's Zane Lowe, DeLonge discussed the decision to donate all of the song's profits to the charity:<blockquote>\u201cI\u2019ve handed out food on holidays and for people in need. I\u2019ve gone to schools and handed out food to a lot of these kids only get their meals at school. And a lot of people think that the United States obviously is a more wealthy country than other, but there\u2019s still so much poverty here. As you know, you live in Los Angeles, and so you can see that there\u2019s a disparity between the classes. It was very simple for me to make one phone call and say, \u2018Why don\u2019t we do this? Because this is something that everybody needs right now. People can\u2019t take care of their families. Kids are not in schools where they\u2019re getting their only meal of the day.\u2019 It kind of worked out, and that\u2019s how you know it\u2019s meant to be. I\u2019m super proud to be with Feeding America on this.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/angels-and-airwaves-new-song-all-thats-left-is-love-985262/|title=Angels and Airwaves Unveil New Song 'All That's Left Is Love'|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|last2=Kreps|first2=Daniel|date=2020-04-16|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref></blockquote>The song was met with mostly positive feedback. [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s Gil Kaufman felt that the song's second verse \"pretty well sums up what a lot of us are feeling these days\" in reference to the social impact of the pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/9359780/angels-and-airwaves-all-thats-left-is-love|title=Angels & Airwaves&#39; &#39;All That&#39;s Left Is Love&#39; Single: Listen|date=2020-04-16|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Josiah Hughes of [[Exclaim!]] called the song \"another inspiring piece of uplifting alt pop. The song is four minutes long, but never overstays its welcome as it builds and expands.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/tom_delonges_angels_and_airwaves_return_with_hopeful_new_single_all_thats_left_is_love|title=Tom DeLonge's Angels & Airwaves Return with Hopeful New Single \"All That's Left Is Love\"|website=exclaim.ca|language=en-ca|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Emily Tan of [[Spin (magazine)|SPIN]] felt that the song \"starts off slow, but then grows into a pretty empowering anthem.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2020/04/angels-airwaves-make-epic-return-with-all-thats-left-is-love/|title=Angels & Airwaves Drop 'All That's Left Is Love'|date=2020-04-16|website=Spin|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n\n* '''Digital download'''<ref>{{Citation|title=All That's Left Is Love - Single by Angels & Airwaves|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/all-thats-left-is-love-single/1507962753|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n# \"All That's Left Is Love\" \u2013 4:05\n\n== Personnel ==\n'''Angels & Airwaves'''\n\n* [[Tom DeLonge]] \u2013 vocals, keyboards, synthesizers, [[songwriting]], [[Record producer|producer]]\n* [[Ilan Rubin]] \u2013 drums, backing vocals, guitars, bass guitar, keyboards, songwriting, producer\n* [[David Kennedy (musician)|David Kennedy]] \u2013 producer\n\n'''Production'''<ref>{{Citation|last